value.value: An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by delayed repolarization of the heart following a heartbeat increases the risk of episodes of torsade de pointes (TDP, a form of irregular heartbeat that originates from the ventricles).
A sleep disorder that involves involuntarily grinding or clenching of the teeth while sleeping.
A chronic lymphocytic leukemia that is characterized by over production of B cells (lymphocytes) by the bone marrow where the B cells appear hairy under a microscope.
A thyroid gland disease that is characterized by elevated thyroxine levels in the blood.

value.value: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that is characterized by abnormally low levels of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (abbreviated G6PD or G6PDH).
An endometrial carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.
A endometrial cancer that is located_in the tissue lining the uterus.
A laryngeal carcinoma that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.
A larynx cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from embryonic mesoderm.
A uterine disease that is characterized by the presence of endometrial tissue grows outside of the endometrium, such as into the myometrium.
A male reproductive organ benign neoplasm that derives_from glandular epithelial cells and that is located_in the prostate.
A male reproductive organ benign neoplasm that derives_from smooth muscle cells and that is located_in the prostate.
A female reproductive system disease characterized by the growth of endometrial tissue outside the uterine body.
An endocrine organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the thyroid and derives_from glandular epithelial cells.
A cervix carcinoma that is located_in the exocervix.
A cervical cancer that is located_in the cervix uteri or located_in the cervical area and that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells.

A syndrome that is characterized by incomplete development of the ear, nose, soft palate, lip, and mandible. It is associated with anomalous development of the first branchial arch and second branchial arch.
A syndrome that is characterized by bilateral and symmetric downslanting palpebral fissures, malar hypoplasia, micrognathia, and external ear abnormalities.
A pancreatitis that is characterized by inflammation of the pancreas over a short period of time and has symptoms of severe abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, fever, and shock.
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the immune system.

A hypersensitivity reaction disease that is characterized by a cell-mediated response to antigens, where Th1 helper T cells react with antigens on antigen-presenting cells and cause a delayed type immune response.
A hypersensitivity reaction type IV disease that involves large amounts of cryoglobulins in the blood which become thick or gel-like in cold temperatures.
A nephritis that causes inflammation of the glomeruli located_in kidney.
A syndrome that is characterized by large cutaneous hemangiomata with hypertrophy of the related bones and soft tissues.

A viral infectious disease that results_in infection in birds and humans, has_material_basis_in Avian orthoavulavirus 1, which is transmitted_by contact with feces and urine of an infected bird, or transmitted_by fomites. The infection has_symptom conjunctivitis, has_symptom headache, and has_symptom lacrimation in humans, and has_symptom gasping, has_symptom coughing, has_symptom twisting of head and neck, has_symptom circling, has_symptom complete paralysis, has_symptom watery diarrhea, and has_symptom reduced egg production in birds.

A viral infectious disease that results_in inflammatory destruction located_in blood vessels of minks and rarely in humans, which has_material_basis_in Aleutian mink disease virus. The infection has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom hepatomegaly, has_symptom enlarged spleen, and has_symptom anemia.

A syndrome characterized by oculocutaneous albinism, immune deficiency, coagulation deficiency and neuropathy and that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the lysosomal trafficking regulator gene (LYST) on chromosome 1q42.
A viral infectious disease that has_material_basis_in Human gammaherpesvirus 4.

A lung disease that is an inflammation of the bronchioles, the smallest air passages of the lungs. It is caused by viruses and bacteria. The disease has_symptom cough, has_symptom wheezing, has_symptom shortness of breath, has_symptom fever, has_symptom nasal flaring in infants and has_symptom bluish skin due to lack of oxygen.

A Coronavirus infectious disease that results_in infection located_in respiratory tract, has_material_basis_in SARS coronavirus (SARS-CoV), which is transmitted_by droplet spread of respiratory secretions, transmitted_by ingestion of contaminated food, or transmitted_by fomites. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom body aches, has_symptom dry cough, and has_symptom hypoxia.
An ocular cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells, derives_from epithelial cells and arises_from the tissues that cover structures located_in the eye.
An auditory system disease that is located in the part of the ear that contains organs of the senses of hearing and equilibrium.

A tuberculosis that is a contagious disease located_in lungs. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom cough, has_symptom difficulty in breathing, has_symptom inflammatory infiltrations, has_symptom formation of tubercles, has_symptom caseation, has_symptom pleural effusion, and has_symptom fibrosis.
A B cell deficiency that is characterized by relative predominance of certain immunoglobulin subtypes and deficiencies of others.
A trichothiodystrophy characterized by skin that is extremely sensitive to ultraviolet (UV) rays from sunlight.

A syndrome that is characterized by an abnormally small head size (microcephaly), a failure to gain weight and grow at the expected rate (failure to thrive) leading to very short stature, and delayed development.
